Privacy Policy for BullViability

Last updated: 03.07.2026

BullViability ("the App") is an independent mobile application designed to help users create and manage cryptocurrency exit strategies. We are committed to protecting your privacy and being transparent about how your information is handled.

1. Information We Collect

The App collects only the information necessary to provide its features and improve reliability.

Contact Information
Email address
Used to identify your account and synchronize your subscription status through RevenueCat.
We do not use your email address for marketing purposes.
Purchase Information

If you purchase BullViability Pro, subscription status and purchase entitlement are processed through Apple App Store / Google Play and RevenueCat.

The App never receives or stores:

payment card numbers;
bank account information;
payment credentials.
Analytics

The App uses Google Firebase Analytics to collect anonymous information about how users interact with the application, including:

app launches;
feature usage;
screen views;
general interaction events.

This information helps improve the user experience.

Crash Reports

The App uses Firebase Crashlytics to automatically collect crash reports and diagnostic information, including:

crash logs;
device model;
operating system version;
application version.

Crash reports are used solely to improve stability and reliability.

2. Information We Do Not Collect

BullViability does not collect or store:

cryptocurrency private keys;
wallet seed phrases;
wallet passwords;
exchange credentials;
bank account information;
payment card information;
government-issued identification documents.

Portfolio information remains stored locally on your device unless future backup features are explicitly enabled by you.

3. How We Use Information

Collected information is used only to:

provide access to BullViability Pro;
verify subscription status;
improve application stability;
understand anonymous usage patterns;
diagnose crashes and technical issues.
4. Third-Party Services

BullViability uses trusted third-party services:

RevenueCat (subscription management)
Google Firebase Analytics
Firebase Crashlytics
CoinMarketCap API
CoinGecko API (where applicable)
Binance API (where applicable)

These services process data according to their own privacy policies.

5. Data Sharing

BullViability does not sell personal information.

Personal information is shared only when necessary to provide application functionality through the third-party services listed above.

6. Data Security

Reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational measures are used to protect your information.

While no method of electronic storage is completely secure, we continuously work to improve security practices.

7. Your Rights

You may request deletion of your account-related information by contacting us at:

bullviability@gmail.com

Please note that certain anonymous analytics or crash reports may not be individually removable because they contain no personally identifiable information.

8. Children's Privacy

BullViability is not intended for children under the age of 13 and does not knowingly collect personal information from children.

